title: Statement by the Press Secretary on H.R. 5128 and H.R. 5139 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
June 08, 2010

 



Statement by the Press Secretary on H.R. 5128 and H.R. 5139




On Tuesday, June 08, 2010, the President signed into law:
H.R. 5128, which designates the United States Department of the Interior Building as the Stewart Lee Udall Department of the Interior Building; 
H.R. 5139, the “Extending Immunities to the Office of the High Representative in Bosnia and Herzegovina and the International Civilian Office in Kosovo Act of 2010.”
